MDCK cells were mock infected or infected (MOI = 3) with the indicated PR8 viruses. At 14 h post-infection, cells were fixed with 4% paraformaldehyde (PFA) and permeabilized with 0.5% Triton X-100 in PBS for 15 min at room temperature. Immunostaining was performed as described previously (
 Nogales et al., 2014b, 
 2016a; 
 Breen et al., 2016; 
 Nogales and Martinez-Sobrido, 2016), using primary rabbit polyclonal anti-HA (Sigma; to detect NS1 expression) or mouse monoclonal anti-NP (HB-65) antibodies and FITC-conjugated anti-mouse or anti-rabbit secondary antibodies (Dako). Cell nuclei were stained with 4′,6′-diamidino-2-phenylindole (DAPI, Research Organics). Images were taken with a fluorescence microscope (Nikon Eclipse TE2000).
